Your Honor,

I stand before you today as an individual who has maintained a clean record, never having been involved in criminal activities. I am here to plead guilty for my involvement in a case of bribery. I accepted a total of £4000 in exchange for not publishing an article that revealed a company's misleading carbon emission claims. I acknowledge my role in this offense and take full responsibility for my actions.

While I regret my involvement in this act of bribery, I must emphasize that the impact of my actions was limited. The information I chose to withhold merely allowed the company to continue their deceptive practices for a short period of time. However, it is important to note that the true numbers were eventually exposed by another source just five weeks later, rendering my role in this offense ultimately inconsequential.

In considering the circumstances of my involvement, I played a passive role in accepting the bribe. I did not initiate the exchange, nor did I actively seek out the opportunity to accept money in return for my silence. However, I understand that accepting the bribe was wrong and I sincerely regret my decision.

As I reflect upon the consequences of my actions, I am committed to making amends and taking the necessary steps to rectify the harm caused. I understand the gravity of my wrongdoing, and I am prepared to cooperate fully with any measures deemed appropriate by the court, including financial restitution or any other form of compensation.

In conclusion, I plead guilty for the offense of bribery and accept the consequences of my actions. I have shared the details of my involvement, expressed remorse for the harm caused, and expressed my commitment to taking responsibility for my actions. Thank you, Your Honor.
